WEBVTT

00:00:00.340 --> 00:00:01.540
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

00:00:01.540 --> 00:00:02.910
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

00:00:02.910 --> 00:00:05.310
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

00:00:06.010 --> 00:00:09.380
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:11.080
(Episode 10)

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:14.420
This is Choi Yu Na.

00:00:16.490 --> 00:00:18.160
I'm willing to do whatever you ask,

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:20.190
Chairman Park.

00:00:22.130 --> 00:00:24.830
Yes. I'll do anything you ask.

00:00:35.610 --> 00:00:36.610
Yes, Dr. Baek.

00:00:37.810 --> 00:00:39.240
I'll be there, no matter what.

00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:41.850
I'll be there to collect
the evidence my sister left behind.

00:00:43.420 --> 00:00:45.350
The bloody pearl she had
in her hand.

00:00:48.220 --> 00:00:50.660
Okay, I'll see you then.

00:00:54.990 --> 00:00:57.500
Are you sure it's safe
for you to go yourself?

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.700
I know it'll be difficult
with them watching.

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:05.870
But I want to be the one
to get it back.

00:01:07.510 --> 00:01:09.470
It's the evidence
that will expose the murder,

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:12.310
but it's also all I have left
of my sister.

00:01:13.310 --> 00:01:14.550
Okay, I get it.

00:01:15.550 --> 00:01:17.680
If that's how you feel,
I'll be extra careful.

00:01:19.250 --> 00:01:21.720
Honestly, it's always weighed
on my conscience.

00:01:22.790 --> 00:01:25.120
Because I was a step too slow,
they took the evidence.

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:27.090
That's why you had to go this far.

00:01:27.960 --> 00:01:29.060
I've always felt so bad about it.

00:01:29.790 --> 00:01:30.800
No, don't say that.

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:33.530
It was all my choice.

00:01:34.370 --> 00:01:37.570
I couldn't have made it this far
without you.

00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:46.540
We'll...

00:01:47.250 --> 00:01:48.750
get the evidence
my sister left behind,

00:01:49.550 --> 00:01:50.750
right?

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:53.320
Of course.

00:01:53.650 --> 00:01:56.220
This time,
Dr. Baek is stepping in to help,

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:59.090
and we've already found a way
to avoid surveillance.

00:02:00.090 --> 00:02:01.990
There's no way
I'm letting them take it this time.

00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:03.800
So don't worry.

00:02:29.320 --> 00:02:30.320
Hold on.

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:32.620
So...

00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:35.760
What you want me to do is...

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:40.900
What, getting cold feet?

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:46.970
It'll just be
a minor car accident, right?

00:02:47.670 --> 00:02:49.640
While those two are in the hospital
and everyone's distracted,

00:02:50.380 --> 00:02:51.480
you'll take over the company.

00:02:52.740 --> 00:02:53.750
There isn't...

00:02:54.550 --> 00:02:56.310
more to the plan than that,
is there?

00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:00.620
What, are you afraid I'll kill them?

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:13.800
I told you,
it's nothing that serious.

00:03:15.030 --> 00:03:17.140
Just think of it
as a minor accident...

00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:19.500
and brush it off.

00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:26.910
So, what's your father like?

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:38.120
Are you going to ignore me?

00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:46.460
Excuse me.

00:03:47.830 --> 00:03:48.930
Compliments of the house.

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:51.000
Thanks.

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:56.870
Don't you eat that.

00:03:59.210 --> 00:04:01.810
You remembered
I'm allergic to chestnuts?

00:04:05.950 --> 00:04:07.790
You care that I don't get sick,

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:09.790
but won't even answer my question?

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:14.330
Park Min Jun,
am I talking to a brick wall?

00:04:15.930 --> 00:04:16.930
He's like a wall.

00:04:18.030 --> 00:04:20.330
He's someone
no one in my family can defy.

00:04:21.470 --> 00:04:23.400
He's like an insurmountable wall.

00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:26.500
That's the kind of man my father is.

00:04:28.670 --> 00:04:29.740
And yet...

00:04:32.140 --> 00:04:34.180
you're thinking about
jumping that wall in complete chaos.

00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:36.550
The power
of the Baek Jin Ju effect, I see.

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:40.490
So your dad's against Min Jun
studying abroad too?

00:04:41.750 --> 00:04:43.150
I'd bet on it.

00:04:43.490 --> 00:04:45.820
He gets furious
when someone decides things...

00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:47.630
without asking him.

00:04:48.690 --> 00:04:50.460
And he's ruthless,
even with his own family.

00:04:55.900 --> 00:04:58.300
Hey, are you sure
you're going to be okay?

00:04:58.540 --> 00:05:01.040
Father's warning
at the family meeting was brutal.

00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:05.310
I doubt you can just ignore it
and get away with it.

00:05:12.650 --> 00:05:13.750
Maybe we should...

00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.490
give up on studying abroad.

00:05:20.990 --> 00:05:21.990
Give up?

00:05:23.460 --> 00:05:25.830
First your design work,
and now studying abroad?

00:05:30.270 --> 00:05:32.000
Didn't you say
we'd find a way together?

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:34.640
You're throwing away
the watch you made for me...

00:05:34.710 --> 00:05:37.810
and the promise we made that easily?

00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:40.280
That's not what I meant.

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:47.320
I'm not giving them up
like they're nothing.

00:05:47.950 --> 00:05:49.120
It's more like...

00:05:50.690 --> 00:05:53.190
I don't want to lose
what really matters.

00:05:54.690 --> 00:05:55.960
I know you wouldn't understand.

00:05:58.630 --> 00:06:00.160
Wait. Hey!

00:06:03.070 --> 00:06:06.040
What was that?
Did you guys just get in a fight?

00:06:09.310 --> 00:06:10.710
Why are you just sitting here?

00:06:11.610 --> 00:06:13.540
Aren't you going after her?
You're just going to let her go?

00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:24.290
Fine. Don't come crying to me
when you regret it later.

00:06:33.600 --> 00:06:34.730
Darn.

00:07:08.830 --> 00:07:10.700
It'll just be
a minor car accident, right?

00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:14.770
What, are you afraid I'll kill them?

00:07:22.950 --> 00:07:26.380
Right. He said
it'd just be a minor accident.

00:07:27.650 --> 00:07:28.650
A minor accident.

00:07:30.590 --> 00:07:31.590
But...

00:07:33.990 --> 00:07:35.360
what if it's not?

00:07:42.430 --> 00:07:45.770
Call her, or go find her yourself.

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.540
I'm telling you,
as someone who saw the whole thing,

00:07:51.380 --> 00:07:52.640
you were in the wrong.

00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:55.580
You think she's happy
about having her design stolen?

00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:58.120
What about turning down
the jewelry school she got into?

00:07:58.120 --> 00:07:59.250
You think that's easy?

00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:02.920
But to her, friendship mattered more
than the design,

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:05.560
and you mattered more
than studying abroad.

00:08:07.330 --> 00:08:08.430
I know.

00:08:08.790 --> 00:08:11.400
If you know, then go apologize.
What's the big deal?

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:13.630
What am I supposed to say?

00:08:16.700 --> 00:08:18.470
This is the first time
Jin Ju and I have ever fought,

00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:21.070
so I have no idea what to say.

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:24.580
I've been racking my brain,
but I can't think of anything.

00:08:25.180 --> 00:08:27.010
Seriously? Just, wow.

00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:29.280
Man, you're hopeless.

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:32.980
Listen up, my clueless brother.

00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:36.720
The point isn't to say
what you want to say.

00:08:36.720 --> 00:08:40.160
It's to say what she wants to hear.

00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:42.690
What she wants to hear?

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:45.400
She probably just wants
to hear one thing.

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:47.600
"I'm sorry."

00:08:47.830 --> 00:08:50.870
Say that,
and she'll understand everything...

00:08:52.440 --> 00:08:55.770
That's right. Get going.
Hurry up and go.

00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:58.680
Knowing Baek Jin Ju,

00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:01.450
she'll totally understand.

00:09:05.750 --> 00:09:08.290
Man, that Park Min Jun
is so clueless.

00:09:08.690 --> 00:09:10.820
I really came through
for him this time.

00:09:14.290 --> 00:09:15.790
While I'm on a roll,

00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:17.900
maybe I should help out
a little more?

00:09:20.630 --> 00:09:22.930
How'd you know I was on my way
to see Director Seo?

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:25.640
I heard you on the phone
this morning.

00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:30.370
"Director Seo, the succession war
has just begun."

00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:32.980
"This is no time
to be playing golf."

00:09:32.980 --> 00:09:34.550
"We needed a plan yesterday!"

00:09:34.550 --> 00:09:35.710
"A plan!"

00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:38.750
Oh my, what's gotten into you?

00:09:38.850 --> 00:09:41.090
Since when do you care
who I'm meeting?

00:09:41.820 --> 00:09:44.320
Are you finally interested
in the succession?

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:47.360
Well, I guess you could say that.

00:09:47.930 --> 00:09:49.190
No way.

00:09:49.930 --> 00:09:51.730
My dear son.

00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:55.970
That bombshell your father dropped
finally knocked some sense into you.

00:09:56.430 --> 00:09:58.440
Yes, that's more like it.

00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:04.710
Speaking of which, Ms. Oh,
could I bring something up?

00:10:04.980 --> 00:10:07.110
If this gets sorted out,

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:09.810
I might actually take an interest
in the company.

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:12.080
What is it? Just say the word.

00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:13.750
I'll take care of it right away.

00:10:14.390 --> 00:10:15.390
What is it?

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:20.990
A reevaluation?

00:10:21.730 --> 00:10:23.460
Why is my work
the only one being reviewed?

00:10:24.030 --> 00:10:25.830
We received a tip that the design
you submitted for the final round...

00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:29.070
was actually someone else's.

00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:33.640
That's not true.
There must be some mistake.

00:10:34.670 --> 00:10:37.170
The person making the claim
says it's their design,

00:10:37.170 --> 00:10:38.680
so we need to verify it.

00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.180
What?

00:10:41.010 --> 00:10:42.210
The accuser...

00:10:42.750 --> 00:10:44.620
claimed it's their own design?

00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:47.790
The review board meets in a week.

00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:49.450
Please make sure you're there.

00:10:54.660 --> 00:10:55.960
Baek Jin Ju.

00:10:56.630 --> 00:10:59.630
After looking down on me
and acting all innocent,

00:11:00.730 --> 00:11:02.330
you're stabbing me in the back?

00:11:05.470 --> 00:11:06.470
Fine.

00:11:07.910 --> 00:11:09.840
Looks like we're going to have
to see each other.

00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:23.890
Yu Na.

00:11:28.590 --> 00:11:30.260
This should be the right place.

00:11:30.800 --> 00:11:32.660
There's the competition
and a few other things,

00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:34.830
so I'd like to talk to you.

00:11:35.900 --> 00:11:38.040
Can you come meet me here?

00:12:38.530 --> 00:12:41.470
The person you have called
is unavailable.

00:12:42.670 --> 00:12:44.300
Is she still mad at me?

00:12:50.640 --> 00:12:53.180
Come on, Baek Jin Ju. Please answer.

00:12:59.620 --> 00:13:00.650
Excuse me.

00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:03.820
Are you one of Jin Ju's friends?

00:13:04.690 --> 00:13:05.690
Sorry?

00:13:05.690 --> 00:13:08.060
I'm sure
I heard you say Baek Jin Ju.

00:13:09.290 --> 00:13:11.460
I'm her dad.

00:13:13.230 --> 00:13:14.330
Hello, sir.

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:16.730
I'm Park Min Jun.

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:18.740
Park Min Jun?

00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:22.410
Are you the boyfriend
Jin Ju told me about?

00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:32.550
Is Jin Ju here?

00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:35.520
She said she was going out
to meet a friend.

00:13:36.050 --> 00:13:38.320
I just assumed it was her boyfriend.

00:13:38.890 --> 00:13:41.490
What is it?
Did you two miss each other?

00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:42.730
Is she not answering her phone?

00:13:44.200 --> 00:13:47.430
Well, we sort of had a fight
yesterday.

00:13:48.830 --> 00:13:53.170
It was entirely my fault.
That's why I came without calling.

00:13:54.940 --> 00:13:56.010
In that case...

00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:58.010
Why don't you come with me?

00:13:58.010 --> 00:14:00.840
We agreed to meet
at the courier company.

00:14:00.980 --> 00:14:02.850
No, it's okay.

00:14:04.050 --> 00:14:06.320
She'd probably be uncomfortable
seeing me right now.

00:14:06.950 --> 00:14:09.420
She's still so mad
she won't even answer my calls.

00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:13.820
Can you tell her
I came to apologize...

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:16.590
and ask her
to please pick up my call?

00:14:17.800 --> 00:14:18.800
All right.

00:14:19.260 --> 00:14:21.930
I'm sure Jin Ju will cool down
and call you soon.

00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:26.700
Okay. I'll be going then.

00:14:46.290 --> 00:14:47.420
Yes, hello?

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:55.300
(Adele Group, B Wing)

00:14:59.170 --> 00:15:01.910
I'm taking this one.
You, get out of the way.

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:04.910
This is the executive elevator.

00:15:05.140 --> 00:15:07.080
Non-executives should step aside.

00:15:07.580 --> 00:15:08.580
What?

00:15:09.210 --> 00:15:10.410
You have some nerve.

00:15:13.950 --> 00:15:14.950
Ma'am!

00:15:15.090 --> 00:15:16.820
No, I just...

00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:18.260
Ma'am!

00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:21.630
What's wrong with her?
I barely even pushed her.

00:15:21.630 --> 00:15:23.660
There's no way
she'd pass out from that.

00:15:23.660 --> 00:15:26.430
I clearly saw her hit her head.

00:15:26.900 --> 00:15:30.030
- Her head?
- What if she has a concussion?

00:15:30.630 --> 00:15:33.140
Ms. Kim, hang in there. Ma'am!

00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:35.910
Ma'am.

00:15:36.340 --> 00:15:37.780
There's no way...

00:15:41.710 --> 00:15:42.880
(Absolute Rest)

00:15:56.990 --> 00:16:00.160
The doctor said
she needs total rest, and no visitors.

00:16:03.200 --> 00:16:06.570
How hard did you push her
that she got a concussion?

00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:08.540
It was just a tap.

00:16:08.840 --> 00:16:10.710
I'm telling you,
it was barely a push.

00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:15.180
That witch
must be plotting something again.

00:16:15.710 --> 00:16:18.150
You stay right there
and keep a close eye on her.

00:16:18.620 --> 00:16:20.450
Don't even think of coming back.
Stay put.

00:16:21.190 --> 00:16:23.720
What? Okay, fine.

00:16:29.590 --> 00:16:31.100
A light tap, my foot.

00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:33.330
I've been on the receiving end
of that shove.

00:16:40.140 --> 00:16:43.110
I can't even go in.
How long am I supposed to wait here?

00:17:02.060 --> 00:17:04.260
With this, we've shaken Oh Jung Ran
off my tail.

00:17:07.830 --> 00:17:11.140
Perfect. You can still make
your appointment on time.

00:17:25.180 --> 00:17:26.250
Jin Ju?

00:17:27.150 --> 00:17:28.190
Jin Ju!

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:29.990
Jin Ju.

00:17:32.020 --> 00:17:34.190
Are you okay? What happened?

00:17:34.260 --> 00:17:36.030
What are you doing
out here all alone?

00:17:36.830 --> 00:17:40.800
I came to see Yu Na,
and a plant stand fell on me.

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:42.700
What? Yu Na?

00:17:49.510 --> 00:17:50.940
I'm so sorry, Mr. Baek.

00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:53.180
What on earth happened?

00:17:54.810 --> 00:17:55.950
My dad...

00:17:56.610 --> 00:17:58.850
He told me to beg Jin Ju.

00:17:59.080 --> 00:18:01.520
He said you'd go easy on him
if she said something.

00:18:02.590 --> 00:18:05.420
So he told me to bring Jin Ju here,

00:18:06.290 --> 00:18:08.590
but then a plant stand
suddenly fell over.

00:18:08.730 --> 00:18:11.130
Then you should've taken her
straight to the hospital.

00:18:11.530 --> 00:18:13.230
I already had to beg her,

00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:15.470
and then she ended up getting hurt.

00:18:16.270 --> 00:18:18.940
He said you'd never forgive us
if you found out,

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:22.070
so we should treat her first
and call you after.

00:18:24.110 --> 00:18:26.410
So, where is your father now?

00:18:27.680 --> 00:18:29.810
He went out to get a doctor.

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:33.950
But the more I thought about it,
it didn't feel right,

00:18:33.950 --> 00:18:35.920
so I called you.

00:18:36.550 --> 00:18:38.020
I'm so sorry, Mr. Baek.

00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:41.020
I'll take Jin Ju to the hospital.

00:18:41.260 --> 00:18:43.730
When your father gets back,
have him call me.

00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:47.160
Let's go.

00:18:48.300 --> 00:18:50.270
You okay? Careful.

00:19:01.610 --> 00:19:04.180
Careful. Easy does it.

00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:11.290
Watch your step.

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:42.820
I'm not doing anything wrong.

00:20:03.170 --> 00:20:04.710
Dad.

00:20:06.040 --> 00:20:07.780
Yu Na's dad...

00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:09.550
Don't you dare defend him.

00:20:10.580 --> 00:20:12.120
He secretly tried
to sell the company,

00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:13.650
and now you're hurt.

00:20:14.590 --> 00:20:16.650
I'm going to make him pay
for what he's done,

00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:18.560
so you just worry about
getting better.

00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:22.030
Are you dizzy?

00:20:22.460 --> 00:20:24.230
How bad is your leg?

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:34.440
Dad...

00:20:34.970 --> 00:20:37.340
I actually really like this scar.

00:20:38.310 --> 00:20:39.540
What's to like about it?

00:20:40.580 --> 00:20:42.310
It scarred your foot.

00:20:42.310 --> 00:20:44.250
How could I, your father,

00:20:44.310 --> 00:20:45.880
let you get a burn like that?

00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:49.820
Even now, my heart breaks
whenever I see that scar.

00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:54.690
Come on, this scar is the reason
you got back on your feet.

00:20:58.360 --> 00:20:59.400
After Mom...

00:21:00.400 --> 00:21:02.000
passed away,

00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:05.200
you would just lie in bed all day,
staring at the ceiling.

00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:08.210
But when I scalded myself
with hot water,

00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:10.470
you jumped out of bed
and found your strength again.

00:21:13.280 --> 00:21:16.610
So every time I look at this scar,

00:21:16.850 --> 00:21:19.550
I'm grateful, because it feels like
it brought my dad back to me.

00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:23.950
Do you have any idea
how worried I was on the way here?

00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:28.830
I was so worried about you,
my mind went blank. I couldn't...

00:21:31.930 --> 00:21:33.000
Oh no.

00:21:33.630 --> 00:21:34.770
My meeting.

00:21:57.550 --> 00:21:59.960
I should have at least called
to say I was running late.

00:22:00.790 --> 00:22:03.090
You can just call them now.

00:22:04.130 --> 00:22:05.760
The hospital is right
around the corner.

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:08.070
I'll call
while you're getting treated.

00:22:09.200 --> 00:22:10.230
By the way,

00:22:10.270 --> 00:22:12.970
you might want to call
your boyfriend too.

00:22:13.300 --> 00:22:14.340
Min Jun?

00:22:15.110 --> 00:22:17.540
He came by the hotel
to say he wanted to apologize.

00:22:17.970 --> 00:22:20.680
He left really worried
since you weren't answering your phone.

00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:23.150
Wait. Really?

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:28.720
Oh no. What do I do?

00:22:30.820 --> 00:22:32.420
I think I lost my phone.

00:22:34.190 --> 00:22:37.530
Min Jun must be worried
I'm not picking up.

00:22:40.060 --> 00:22:42.470
If you're so worried about him,
why did you fight to begin with?

00:22:43.370 --> 00:22:45.070
What? It was because of this watch.

00:22:46.670 --> 00:22:48.910
Oh no, my watch!

00:22:51.070 --> 00:22:52.410
What about your watch?

00:22:54.510 --> 00:22:56.250
Oh no.

00:22:58.650 --> 00:23:00.620
You've got to be kidding me.

00:23:06.460 --> 00:23:07.460
Actually,

00:23:07.890 --> 00:23:09.990
this was mainly
because I said I wanted...

00:23:10.690 --> 00:23:12.400
to give up studying abroad.

00:23:13.300 --> 00:23:14.630
Why would you give that up?

00:23:16.100 --> 00:23:18.770
I was worried because Min Jun's parents
don't want him...

00:23:19.070 --> 00:23:20.140
to study abroad.

00:23:21.300 --> 00:23:23.910
I hear his father is intimidating.

00:23:24.110 --> 00:23:26.310
It reminded me of what you said.

00:23:27.310 --> 00:23:29.910
"It could be more dangerous
than you think."

00:23:39.320 --> 00:23:40.760
I'm following them now.

00:23:42.260 --> 00:23:43.890
I'll see what happens...

00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:45.960
and call you right back.

00:23:54.840 --> 00:23:56.570
Min Jun's father is...

00:23:56.570 --> 00:23:59.010
Chairman Park Tae Ho of Adele Group.

00:23:59.880 --> 00:24:02.250
What? Adele Group?

00:24:02.950 --> 00:24:04.350
He's the son
of Adele Group's chairman?

00:24:07.680 --> 00:24:10.190
When's his birthday?

00:24:10.690 --> 00:24:13.090
The same as mine. Crazy, right?

00:24:13.690 --> 00:24:16.230
- Dad, watch the road.
- Oh, right.

00:24:16.790 --> 00:24:18.700
Adele Group's chairman's son...

00:24:19.100 --> 00:24:20.930
who has the same birthday as Jin Ju?

00:24:22.770 --> 00:24:23.930
Both babies...

00:24:25.340 --> 00:24:27.600
were born the same day,
at the exact same time.

00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:36.010
I can't believe
they found each other.

00:24:36.750 --> 00:24:38.950
Who found who? What do you mean?

00:24:46.660 --> 00:24:47.660
Dad.

00:24:55.730 --> 00:24:56.770
Dad!

00:25:01.740 --> 00:25:02.740
Dad!

00:25:04.570 --> 00:25:07.280
Don't worry.
I think the gas pedal is stuck.

00:25:07.480 --> 00:25:09.680
I'll run us into the railing
to stop the car.

00:25:22.530 --> 00:25:25.060
Jin Ju, hold on tight. It's no use.

00:25:25.230 --> 00:25:27.430
I'll have to crash into something
over there too.

00:25:30.970 --> 00:25:32.800
Dad, watch out.

00:25:50.250 --> 00:25:52.320
- Jin Ju!
- Dad!

00:26:11.540 --> 00:26:13.980
Jin Ju. Baek Jin Ju.

00:26:15.910 --> 00:26:17.150
Dad?

00:26:20.020 --> 00:26:21.320
I'm okay.

00:26:30.030 --> 00:26:33.160
Dad, what is it? Are you hurt?

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:37.030
No, I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

00:26:37.800 --> 00:26:41.500
Dad, just hang on.
I'll call an ambulance.

00:26:45.440 --> 00:26:46.640
Gosh, my phone.

00:26:47.680 --> 00:26:49.710
Dad, you have your phone, right?

00:26:49.980 --> 00:26:50.980
What?

00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:52.750
Right.

00:27:12.500 --> 00:27:13.500
Jin Ju.

00:27:14.870 --> 00:27:17.670
Yes? What is it, Dad?
Are you feeling worse?

00:27:26.550 --> 00:27:27.980
When you call for help,

00:27:28.450 --> 00:27:31.390
you have to give them
our exact location.

00:27:31.490 --> 00:27:33.960
It'll be hard for them to find us
down this embankment.

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:37.430
So go up to the road,
call for help, and wait there.

00:27:46.240 --> 00:27:47.240
Okay.

00:27:47.740 --> 00:27:49.610
Okay, go. Hurry.

00:27:50.070 --> 00:27:52.280
Got it. Hang on, Dad.

00:29:28.810 --> 00:29:31.770
That's it. Hurry on up.

00:29:33.680 --> 00:29:34.910
My Jin Ju,

00:29:36.380 --> 00:29:37.580
no matter what happens,

00:29:38.620 --> 00:29:40.020
you'll be able
to get through anything.

00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:45.490
Jin Ju.

00:29:46.990 --> 00:29:47.990
My daughter.

00:29:50.430 --> 00:29:53.160
Dad loves you so much.

00:30:40.810 --> 00:30:41.810
Dad...

00:30:43.610 --> 00:30:45.250
Dad!

00:30:50.520 --> 00:30:53.720
Dad!

00:30:54.960 --> 00:30:57.890
Dad!

00:31:01.260 --> 00:31:03.600
Dad!

00:31:05.440 --> 00:31:07.800
Dad!

00:31:34.130 --> 00:31:37.100
(Pearl in Red)

00:31:37.500 --> 00:31:40.000
A car accident?
What about Dr. Baek? Is he okay?

00:31:40.070 --> 00:31:42.970
The car exploded,
and his daughter was with him.

00:31:43.070 --> 00:31:45.640
An opportunity like this
is too good to waste,

00:31:45.640 --> 00:31:47.010
wouldn't you agree?

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:51.080
Here is proof
of CEO Baek Jun Gi's embezzlement.

00:31:51.180 --> 00:31:52.650
You planned to kill them all along.

00:31:52.650 --> 00:31:54.650
You used me to kill them both!

00:31:54.650 --> 00:31:58.420
Framing an innocent person
without evidence is a crime!

00:31:58.420 --> 00:32:01.290
Just go ahead
and enjoy the things you've stolen.

00:32:01.360 --> 00:32:03.030
Jin Ju. Baek Jin Ju.

00:32:03.030 --> 00:32:04.830
My daughter, it's time you woke up.

00:32:07.200 --> 00:32:09.200
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)